body:
@awakecoding: valid points, great thinking! 

I've always felt a bit itchy about the native commands. Explaining to newbies; 
"Yes, PS is all verb-noun doctrine...unless...there's also this... no no, they're not aliases! Yes, they do look a bit like *nix style commands. Are you confused...? Well I am also sometimes...still...."

> My main concern is that we certainly don't want a third call operator in the future, so this means we have to get this one right, otherwise we'll face the same issue in a few years.

That's not really fair. In de PS 2/3 days, who would have known that PS is going to be ported to *NIX alike systems? So who knows were we are 5 years from now. Things just...change. 

You cannot design 'for everything'...unless your answer is always 42 when you don't know :smile:
